Bath Abbey.label: Bath Abbey
Bath Abbey.description: The Abbey Church of Saint Peter and Saint Paul, Bath, commonly known as Bath Abbey, is an Anglican parish church and a former Benedictine monastery in Bath, Somerset, England. Wikipedia

All Saints' Church, Wittenberg.label: All Saints' Church, Wittenberg
All Saints' Church, Wittenberg.description: All Saints' Church, commonly referred to as Schloßkirche to distinguish it from the Stadtkirche of St. Mary — and sometimes known as the Reformation Memorial Church — was a Catholic church which later ... Wikipedia

Bradford Cathedral.label: Bradford Cathedral
Bradford Cathedral.description: Bradford Cathedral, full name Cathedral Church of St Peter, is situated in the heart of Bradford in West Yorkshire, England, on a site used for Christian worship since the 8th century when missionaries based in Dewsbury evangelised the region. Wikipedia

Cathedral of La Laguna.label: La Laguna Cathedral
Cathedral of La Laguna.description: The Cathedral of San Cristóbal de La Laguna or Catedral de Nuestra Señora de los Remedios is a Catholic cathedral in Tenerife, Spain. Begun in 1904 and completed in 1915, it is dedicated to the Virgin of Los Remedios. Wikipedia

Cathedral of the Archangel.label: Cathedral of the Archangel
Cathedral of the Archangel.description: The Cathedral of the Archangel is a Russian Orthodox church dedicated to the Archangel Michael. It is located in Cathedral Square of the Moscow Kremlin in Russia between the Great Kremlin Palace and the Ivan the Great Bell Tower. Wikipedia

Chichester Cathedral.label: Chichester Cathedral
Chichester Cathedral.description: The Cathedral Church of the Holy Trinity, otherwise called Chichester Cathedral, is the seat of the Anglican Bishop of Chichester. It is located in Chichester, in Sussex, England. Wikipedia

Christ Church Cathedral, Dublin.label: Christ Church Cathedral, Dublin
Christ Church Cathedral, Dublin.description: Christ Church Cathedral is the cathedral of the United Dioceses of Dublin and Glendalough and the cathedral of the Ecclesiastical province of the United Provinces of Dublin and Cashel in the Church of Ireland. Wikipedia

Dore Abbey.label: Dore Abbey
Dore Abbey.description: Dore Abbey is a former Cistercian abbey in the village of Abbey Dore in the Golden Valley, Herefordshire, England. Wikipedia

Dormition Cathedral, Moscow.label: Dormition Cathedral, Moscow
Dormition Cathedral, Moscow.description: The Cathedral of the Dormition is a Russian Orthodox church dedicated to the Dormition of the Theotokos. Wikipedia

Ginkaku-ji.label: Ginkaku-ji
Ginkaku-ji.description: Ginkaku-ji, officially named Jishō-ji, is a Zen temple in the Sakyo ward of Kyoto, Japan. It is one of the constructions that represent the Higashiyama Culture of Muromachi period. Wikipedia

Kōfuku-ji.label: Kōfuku-ji
Kōfuku-ji.description: Kōfuku-ji is a Buddhist temple in the city of Nara, Japan. The temple is the national headquarters of the Hossō school and is one of the eight Historic Monuments of Ancient Nara inscribed on the UNESCO World Heritage List. Wikipedia

Llandaff Cathedral.label: Llandaff Cathedral
Llandaff Cathedral.description: Llandaff Cathedral is the seat of the Bishop of Llandaff, head of the Church in Wales Diocese of Llandaff. It is situated in the district of Llandaff in the city of Cardiff, the capital of Wales. Wikipedia

Rinnō-ji.label: Rinnō-ji
Rinnō-ji.description: Rinnō-ji is a complex of 15 Buddhist temple buildings in the city of Nikkō, Tochigi Prefecture, Japan. The site was established in the year 766 by the Buddhist monk, Shōdō. Wikipedia

Selby Abbey.label: Selby Abbey
Selby Abbey.description: Selby Abbey is an Anglican parish church in the town of Selby, North Yorkshire, England. Wikipedia

St. Martin's Church, Landshut.label: St. Martin's Church, Landshut
St. Martin's Church, Landshut.description: The Church of St. Martin in Landshut is a medieval church in that German city. St. Martin's Church, along with Trausnitz Castle and the celebration of the Landshuter Hochzeit, are the most important landmarks and historical events of Landshut. Wikipedia

St Albans Cathedral.label: St Albans Cathedral
St Albans Cathedral.description: St Albans Cathedral is a Church of England cathedral church at St Albans, England. At 84 metres, its nave is the longest of any cathedral in England. Wikipedia

St Patrick's Cathedral, Dublin.label: St Patrick's Cathedral, Dublin
St Patrick's Cathedral, Dublin.description: Saint Patrick's Cathedral in Dublin, also known as The National Cathedral and Collegiate Church of Saint Patrick, Dublin, or in the Irish language as Árd Eaglais Naomh Pádraig, founded in 1191, is the ... Wikipedia

Storkyrkan.label: Storkyrkan
Storkyrkan.description: Sankt Nikolai kyrka, most commonly known as Storkyrkan and Stockholms domkyrka, is the oldest church in Gamla Stan, the old town in central Stockholm, Sweden. It is an important example of Swedish Brick Gothic. Wikipedia

Trinity Cathedral, Saint Petersburg.label: Trinity Cathedral, Saint Petersburg
Trinity Cathedral, Saint Petersburg.description: The Trinity Cathedral, sometimes called the Troitsky Cathedral, in Saint Petersburg, Russia, is a late example of the Empire style, built between 1828 and 1835 to a design by Vasily Stasov. Wikipedia

University Church of St Mary the Virgin.label: University Church of St Mary the Virgin
University Church of St Mary the Virgin.description: The University Church of St Mary the Virgin is the largest of Oxford's parish churches and the centre from which the University of Oxford grew. Wikipedia

Westminster Cathedral.label: Westminster Cathedral
Westminster Cathedral.description: Westminster Cathedral in London is the mother church of the Catholic community in England and Wales and the Metropolitan Church and Cathedral of the Archbishop of Westminster. It is dedicated to the "Most Precious Blood of Jesus Christ". Wikipedia

Yakushi-ji.label: Yakushi-ji
Yakushi-ji.description: Yakushi-ji is one of the most famous imperial and ancient Buddhist temples in Japan, located in Nara. The temple is the headquarters of the Hossō school of Japanese Buddhism. Wikipedia

Cathedral of Christ the Saviour.label: Cathedral of Christ the Saviour
Cathedral of Christ the Saviour.description: The Cathedral of Christ the Saviour is a cathedral in Moscow, Russia, on the northern bank of the Moskva River, a few blocks southwest of the Kremlin. With an overall height of 103 metres, it is the tallest Orthodox Christian church in the world. Wikipedia

Daitoku-ji.label: Daitoku-ji
Daitoku-ji.description: Daitoku-ji is a Buddhist temple, one of fourteen autonomous branches of the Rinzai school of Japanese Zen. It is located in Kita-ku, Kyoto, Japan. The "mountain name" 龍宝山). Wikipedia

Hōryū-ji.label: Hōryū-ji
Hōryū-ji.description: Hōryū-ji is a Buddhist temple in Ikaruga, Nara Prefecture, Japan. Its full name is Hōryū Gakumonji, or Learning Temple of the Flourishing Law, the complex serving as both a seminary and monastery. Wikipedia

Myōshin-ji.label: Myōshin-ji
Myōshin-ji.description: Myōshin-ji is a temple complex in Kyoto, Japan, and head temple of the associated branch of Rinzai Zen Buddhism. Wikipedia
Address: 〒616-8035 京都府京都市右京区花園妙心寺町1

Temple of the Six Banyan Trees.label: Temple of the Six Banyan Trees
Temple of the Six Banyan Trees.description: The Temple of the Six Banyan Trees is an ancient Buddhist temple originally built in 537 in the Liang Dynasty in Guangzhou, southern China. Wikipedia

Wells Cathedral.label: Wells Cathedral
Wells Cathedral.description: Wells Cathedral is a Church of England place of worship in Wells, Somerset dedicated to St Andrew the Apostle, and is the seat of the Bishop of Bath and Wells. Wikipedia

Yoido Full Gospel Church.label: Yoido Full Gospel Church
Yoido Full Gospel Church.description: Yoido Full Gospel Church is a Pentecostal church affiliated with the Assemblies of God on Yeouido in Seoul, South Korea. With about 1,000,000 members, it is the largest Pentecostal Christian congregation in South Korea, and the world. Wikipedia

Allen Temple AME Church (Cincinnati, Ohi.label: Allen Temple AME Church
Allen Temple AME Church (Cincinnati, Ohi.description: The Allen Temple AME Church in Cincinnati, Ohio, USA, is the mother church of the Third Episcopal District of the African Methodist Episcopal Church. Wikipedia

Crathie Kirk.label: Crathie Kirk
Crathie Kirk.description: Crathie Kirk is a small Church of Scotland parish church in the Scottish village of Crathie, best known for being the regular place of worship of the British Royal Family when they are holidaying at nearby Balmoral Castle. Wikipedia

Worcester Cathedral.label: Worcester Cathedral
Worcester Cathedral.description: Worcester Cathedral, before the English Reformation known as Worcester Priory, is an Anglican cathedral in Worcester, England; situated on a bank overlooking the River Severn. It is the seat of the Bishop of Worcester. Wikipedia

Liverpool Metropolitan Cathedral.label: Liverpool Metropolitan Cathedral
Liverpool Metropolitan Cathedral.description: Metropolitan Cathedral of Christ the King is the cathedral of the Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Liverpool in Liverpool, England. The cathedral is the seat of the Archbishop of Liverpool. Wikipedia

Mount Osore.label: Mount Osore
Mount Osore.description: Mount Osore is a caldera volcano in the center of remote Shimokita Peninsula of Aomori Prefecture, Japan. According to the Smithsonian National Museum of National History, it peaks at 879 meters and its last eruption was noted in 1787. Wikipedia

Saint Thomas Church (New York City).label: St. Thomas Episcopal Church
Saint Thomas Church (New York City).description: Saint Thomas Church, located at the corner of 53rd Street and Fifth Avenue in the borough of Manhattan, New York, New York in the United States, is an Episcopal parish church of the Episcopal Diocese of New York. Wikipedia

Betel Church (Turku).label: Betel Church
Betel Church (Turku).description:
Betel Church is located in the VII District of Turku, Finland. It is a church of the Turku adventism parish.
The jugend style church was completed in 1906 under the plans of Frithiof Strandell. Wikipedia

St John-at-Hampstead.label: St John-at-Hampstead
St John-at-Hampstead.description: St John-at-Hampstead is a Church of England parish church dedicated to St John the Evangelist in Church Row, Hampstead, London. Wikipedia

Bellevue Baptist Church.label: Bellevue Baptist Church
Bellevue Baptist Church.description: Bellevue Baptist Church is a large Southern Baptist megachurch in the Cordova area of Memphis, Tennessee, United States. Bellevue is the largest church in Memphis and is one of the leading churches in the Southern Baptist Convention. Wikipedia

National Presbyterian Church.label: National Presbyterian Church
National Presbyterian Church.description: The National Presbyterian Church is a Christian congregation of approximately 1,800 members of all ages from the greater metropolitan Washington, D.C., area. Wikipedia

All Hallows-by-the-Tower.label: All Hallows-by-the-Tower
All Hallows-by-the-Tower.description: All Hallows-by-the-Tower, also previously dedicated to St. Mary the Virgin and sometimes known as All Hallows Barking, is an ancient Anglican church on Byward Street in the City of London, overlooking the Tower of London. Wikipedia

All Saints' Church, Childwall.label: All Saints' Church, Childwall
All Saints' Church, Childwall.description: All Saints' Church, Childwall, is in Childwall, Liverpool, Merseyside, England. It is designated by English Heritage as a Grade I listed building, and is the only medieval church remaining in the Metropolitan borough of Liverpool. Wikipedia

Arctic Cathedral.label: Arctic Cathedral
Arctic Cathedral.description: The Arctic Cathedral, formally known as Tromsdalen Church or Tromsøysund Church, is a church in the city of Tromsø in Troms county, Norway. Wikipedia

Basilica of St. Hyacinth.label: Basilica of St. Hyacinth
Basilica of St. Hyacinth.description: St. Hyacinth Basilica, formally the Basilica of St. Hyacinth, - historic church of the Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Chicago, located at 3636 West Wolfram Street in Chicago, Illinois. Wikipedia

Basilica of the Sacred Heart of Jesus, P.label: Basilica of the Sacred Heart of Jesus, Pondicherry
Basilica of the Sacred Heart of Jesus, P.description: Basilica of the Sacred Heart of Jesus, situated on the south boulevard of Pondicherry in Puducherry, India, is an oriental specimen of Gothic architecture. Wikipedia

Bodø Cathedral.label: Bodø Cathedral
Bodø Cathedral.description: Bodø Cathedral is a cathedral in the municipality of Bodø in Nordland county, Norway. It is located in the town of Bodø. The church is part of the Bodø parish in the Bodø deanery in the Diocese of Sør-Hålogaland. Wikipedia

Capitol City Baptist Church (West Avenue.label: Capitol City Baptist Church
Capitol City Baptist Church (West Avenue.description: Capitol City Baptist Church is a baptist church located at 111 West Avenue, Quezon City, Philippines. It is one of two baptist churches found along West Avenue, the other being Faith Baptist Church. Wikipedia

Carey Baptist Church.label: Carey Baptist Church
Carey Baptist Church.description: Carey Baptist Church is an independent evangelical/Baptist church in Reading, England. Wikipedia

Cathedral Church of St. James (Toronto).label: Cathedral Church of St. James
Cathedral Church of St. James (Toronto).description: Cathedral Church of St. James in Toronto, Canada is the home of the oldest congregation in the city. The parish was established in 1797. Wikipedia

Cathedral Church of St Marie, Sheffield.label: Cathedral Church of St Marie, Sheffield
Cathedral Church of St Marie, Sheffield.description: The Cathedral Church of St Marie is the Roman Catholic cathedral in Sheffield, England. It lies in a slightly hidden location, just off the main shopping street in the city, but signals its presence with a tall spire. Wikipedia

Cathedral of St Mary and St Anne.label: Cathedral of St Mary and St Anne
Cathedral of St Mary and St Anne.description: The Cathedral of Saint Mary and Saint Anne is a Roman Catholic cathedral located in Cork, Ireland. It is the seat of the Bishop of Cork and Ross, and the mother church of the Roman Catholic Diocese of Cork and Ross. Wikipedia

Cathedral of the Sacred Heart (Pensacola.label: Cathedral of the Sacred Heart
Cathedral of the Sacred Heart (Pensacola.description: The Cathedral of the Sacred Heart, is the seat of the Bishop of the Roman Catholic Diocese of Pensacola-Tallahassee. It shares this distinction with the Co-Cathedral of Saint Thomas More in Tallahassee. Wikipedia

Christ Church, Bath.label: Christ Church, Bath
Christ Church, Bath.description: Christ Church, Bath is a proprietary chapel on Julian Road, Bath, England. Wikipedia

Christ Church, Heaton Norris.label: Christ Church, Heaton Norris
Christ Church, Heaton Norris.description: Christ Church, Heaton Norris, consists of the remains of a redundant Anglican church in Wellington Road, Heaton Norris, Stockport, Greater Manchester, England. Only the tower and part of the walls of the aisles survive. Wikipedia

Christ Church, St Leonards-on-Sea.label: Christ Church, St Leonards-on-Sea
Christ Church, St Leonards-on-Sea.description: Christ Church is an Anglican church in the town and seaside resort of St Leonards-on-Sea, part of the Borough of Hastings in East Sussex, England. Wikipedia

Christ Church Cathedral, Waterford.label: Christ Church Cathedral, Waterford
Christ Church Cathedral, Waterford.description: Christ Church Cathedral, Waterford, or more formally, the Cathedral of The Holy Trinity, Christ Church, is a cathedral of the Church of Ireland in Waterford City, Ireland. It is in the ecclesiastical province of Dublin. Wikipedia

Christ Church Cathedral (Vancouver).label: Christ Church Cathedral
Christ Church Cathedral (Vancouver).description: Christ Church Cathedral, in Vancouver, British Columbia, is the cathedral church of the Anglican Diocese of New Westminster of the Anglican Church of Canada. Wikipedia

Church of Saint John the Baptist, Liverp.label: Church of Saint John the Baptist, Liverpool
Church of Saint John the Baptist, Liverp.description: The Church of Saint John the Baptist, Liverpool, is on the corner of West Derby Road and Green Lane, in Tuebrook, Liverpool, Merseyside, England. Wikipedia

Church of Our Saviour, Copenhagen.label: Church of Our Saviour, Copenhagen
Church of Our Saviour, Copenhagen.description: Church of Our Saviour is a baroque church in Copenhagen, Denmark, most famous for its corkscrew spire with an external winding staircase that can be climbed to the top, offering extensive views over central Copenhagen. Wikipedia

Church of St. Peter, St. Albans.label: Church of St. Peter, St. Albans
Church of St. Peter, St. Albans.description: St Peter's Church in St Albans, England, is a parish church in the Church of England. Wikipedia

Church of St. Agnes and St. Pancras, Tox.label: Church of St. Agnes and St. Pancras, Toxteth Park
Church of St. Agnes and St. Pancras, Tox.description: The Church of St. Agnes and St. Pancras, Toxteth Park, is located in Ullet Road, Toxteth Park, Liverpool, England. Wikipedia

Church of St Clare, Liverpool.label: Church of St Clare, Liverpool
Church of St Clare, Liverpool.description: The Church of St Clare, Liverpool, is located on the corner of Arundel Avenue and York Avenue in the Sefton Park area of Liverpool, Merseyside, England. Wikipedia

Church of the Holy Trinity (Toronto).label: Church of the Holy Trinity
Church of the Holy Trinity (Toronto).description: The Church of the Holy Trinity is an Anglican church in downtown Toronto, Canada at Trinity Square. Wikipedia

Church of the Sacred Heart, Singapore.label: Church of the Sacred Heart, Singapore
Church of the Sacred Heart, Singapore.description: The Church of the Sacred Heart is a Roman Catholic church in the Museum Planning Area of Singapore. Wikipedia

City of Ten Thousand Buddhas.label: City of Ten Thousand Buddhas
City of Ten Thousand Buddhas.description: The City Of Ten Thousand Buddhas is an international Buddhist community and monastery founded by Hsuan Hua, an important figure in Western Buddhism. Wikipedia

Collegium Maius.label: Collegium Maius
Collegium Maius.description: The Collegium Maius, in Kraków Old Town, Poland, is the Jagiellonian University's oldest building, dating back to the 14th century. It stands at the corner of ulica Jagiellońska and ulica Świętej Anny near the main city centre. Wikipedia

Drumcree Church.label: Drumcree Church
Drumcree Church.description: Drumcree Parish Church, officially The Church of the Ascension, is the parish church of Drumcree Church of Ireland parish. The church is within the townland of Drumcree, roughly 1.5 miles to the northeast of Portadown, County Armagh. Wikipedia

Ealing Abbey.label: Ealing Abbey
Ealing Abbey.description: Ealing Abbey is a Roman Catholic Benedictine monastic foundation on Castlebar Hill in Ealing. It is part of the English Benedictine Congregation. Wikipedia

Dream Center.label: Dream Center
Dream Center.description: The Dream Center is a Pentecostal Christian Church mission located at 2301 Bellevue Avenue in the Echo Park neighborhood of Los Angeles, California, two blocks west of Alvarado Street on the north side of the 101 Freeway. Wikipedia

Gokoku-ji.label: Gokoku-ji
Gokoku-ji.description: Gokoku-ji is a Shingon Buddhist temple in Tokyo's Bunkyō. Wikipedia

Elgin Cathedral.label: Elgin Cathedral
Elgin Cathedral.description: Elgin Cathedral, sometimes called The Lantern of the North, is a historic ruin in Elgin, Moray, north-east Scotland. Wikipedia

Grosvenor Chapel.label: Grosvenor Chapel
Grosvenor Chapel.description: Grosvenor Chapel, is an Anglican church in what is now the City of Westminster, England, built in 1730s it inspired many churches in New England. It is situated on South Audley Street in Mayfair. Wikipedia

Hen Church.label: Hen Church
Hen Church.description: Hen Church is a parish church in Rauma Municipality in Møre og Romsdal county, Norway. It is located in the village of Isfjorden. It is about 6 kilometres east of the town of Åndalsnes. Wikipedia

Gothic Protestant Church of Avas.label: Gothic Protestant Church of Avas
Gothic Protestant Church of Avas.description: The Gothic Protestant Church of Avas is the oldest building in the centre of the city of Miskolc in Northern Hungary. It was built in the 13th century as a small, Romanesque style church, and later it was expanded to a larger Gothic style church. Wikipedia

Holy Rosary Cathedral (Vancouver).label: Holy Rosary Cathedral
Holy Rosary Cathedral (Vancouver).description: The Metropolitan Cathedral of Our Lady of the Holy Rosary, commonly known as Holy Rosary Cathedral, is a late 19th-century French Gothic revival church that serves as the cathedral of the Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Vancouver. Wikipedia

Great Malvern Priory.label: Great Malvern Priory
Great Malvern Priory.description: Great Malvern Priory in Malvern, Worcestershire, England, was a Benedictine monastery c.1075-1540 and is now an Anglican parish church. In 1949 it was designated a Grade I listed building. Wikipedia

John's Lane Church.label: John's Lane Church
John's Lane Church.description: John's Lane Church opened in 1874 on the site of St. John's Hospital. It is located on Thomas Street, Dublin, close to the centre of the medieval city, and is served by the Augustinian Order. Wikipedia

Jufuku-ji.label: Jufuku-ji
Jufuku-ji.description: Kikokuzan Kongō Jufuku Zenji, usually known as Jufuku-ji, is a temple of the Kenchō-ji branch of the Rinzai sect and the oldest Zen temple in Kamakura, Kanagawa Prefecture, Japan. Wikipedia
Address: 〒248-0011 神奈川県鎌倉市扇ガ谷１丁目１７−７

Kazan Cathedral, Moscow.label: Kazan Cathedral, Moscow
Kazan Cathedral, Moscow.description: Kazan Cathedral Russian Казанский собор, also known as the "Cathedral of Our Lady of Kazan", is a Russian Orthodox church located on the northeast corner of Red Square in Moscow, Russia. Wikipedia

Kimpusen-ji.label: Kimpusen-ji
Kimpusen-ji.description: Kimpusen-ji is the head temple of a branch of the Shugendō religion called Kimpusen-Shugendō in Yoshino district, Nara prefecture, Japan. Wikipedia

Kotor Cathedral.label: Kotor Cathedral
Kotor Cathedral.description: The Cathedral of Saint Tryphon in Kotor is one of two Roman Catholic cathedrals in Montenegro. It is the seat of the Croatian Catholic Bishopric of Kotor which covers the entire gulf, currently led by Bishop Mons. Ilija Janjić. Wikipedia

Kokutai-ji.label: Kokutai-ji
Kokutai-ji.description: Kokutai-ji, originally Tosho-ji, is one of fourteen autonomous branches of the Rinzai school of Japanese Zen, founded in 1300 by the monk Jiun Myoi in Toyama, Japan. Wikipedia

Living Enrichment Center.label: Living Enrichment Center
Living Enrichment Center.description: Living Enrichment Center was a New Thought megachurch and retreat center in the U.S. state of Oregon. Wikipedia

Manchester Cathedral.label: Manchester Cathedral
Manchester Cathedral.description: Manchester Cathedral or the Cathedral and Collegiate Church of St Mary, St Denys and St George in Manchester, England is the mother church of the Anglican Diocese of Manchester, seat of the bishop and the city's parish church. Wikipedia

Manordeifi Old Church.label: Manordeifi Old Church
Manordeifi Old Church.description: Manordeifi Old Church is a redundant church in Manordeifi, Pembrokeshire, Wales. It is designated by Cadw as a Grade II* listed building, and is under the care of the Friends of Friendless Churches. Wikipedia

Mars Hill Church.label: Mars Hill Church
Mars Hill Church.description: Mars Hill Church is a Christian megachurch based in Seattle, Washington and with 15 locations in 5 U.S. states. Wikipedia

Narita-san.label: Narita-san
Narita-san.description: Narita-san Shinshō-ji is a Shingon Buddhist temple located in central Narita, Chiba, Japan. It was founded in 940 by Kanchō Daisōjō, a disciple of Kōbō Daishi. Wikipedia

Nativity Cathedral, Chișinău.label: Nativity Cathedral, Chișinău
Nativity Cathedral, Chișinău.description: The Cathedral of Christ's Nativity is the main cathedral of the Moldovan Orthodox Church in Central Chișinău, Moldova. Wikipedia

Engaku-ji.label: Engaku-ji
Engaku-ji.description:
Not to be confused with Enryaku-ji in Kyoto.
Zuirokuzan Engaku Kōshō Zenji, or Engaku-ji, is one of the most important Zen Buddhist temple complexes in Japan and is ranked second among Kamakura's Five Mountains. Wikipedia
Address: 〒247-0247 神奈川県鎌倉市山ノ内409

Negoro-ji.label: Negoro-ji
Negoro-ji.description: The Negoro-ji complex of Buddhist temples stands on the side of, and is surrounded by, the sacred peaks of the Katsuragi Mountains which dominate the horizon at the northern end of the city of Iwade, Wakayama in Japan. Wikipedia

Rochester Cathedral.label: Rochester Cathedral
Rochester Cathedral.description: Rochester Cathedral, or the Cathedral Church of Christ and the Blessed Virgin Mary, is a Norman church in Rochester, Medway. The bishopric is the second oldest in England after Canterbury. It is a Grade I listed building. Wikipedia

Noto Cathedral.label: Noto Cathedral
Noto Cathedral.description: Noto Cathedral is a Roman Catholic cathedral in Noto in Sicily, Italy. Its construction, in the style of the Sicilian Baroque, began in the early 18th century and was completed in 1776. Wikipedia

Sagami-ji.label: Sagami-ji
Sagami-ji.description: Sagami-ji, is a Shingon Buddhist temple in Kasai, Hyōgo Prefecture, Japan. Its mountain name is Senjōsan. Emperor Shōmu ordered its construction in the 17th year of the Tenpyō era, at the request of Gyōki, a Buddhist priest. Wikipedia

Seichō-ji.label: Seichō-ji
Seichō-ji.description: Seichō-ji, alternately called Kiyosumi-dera from an alternative pronunciation of the kanji in its name, is a Nichiren Shū temple located in the city of Kamogawa in Chiba Prefecture, Japan. Wikipedia

Saint Lucy Parish, Campbell, California.label: Saint Lucy Parish
Saint Lucy Parish, Campbell, California.description: St. Lucy Catholic Parish is the Roman Catholic parish church of the Latin Rite in Campbell, California. The church was originally established as a Mission of Saint Martin Parish of San Jose in 1914. The current church was built in 1957. Wikipedia

Rijeka Cathedral.label: Rijeka Cathedral
Rijeka Cathedral.description:
The St. Vitus Cathedral is a Roman Catholic cathedral in Rijeka, Croatia.
The Church of St. Vitus was in Middle Ages a small and one-sided, romanesque church dedicated to the patron saint and protector of Rijeka. Wikipedia

Seiganto-ji.label: Seiganto-ji
Seiganto-ji.description: Seiganto-ji is a Tendai Buddhist temple in Wakayama Prefecture, Japan. In 2004, it was listed as a UNESCO World Heritage Site along with other locations, under the name "Sacred Sites and Pilgrimage Routes in the Kii Mountain Range". Wikipedia
Address: 〒649-5301 和歌山県東牟婁郡那智勝浦町大字那智山８
